      "content": {
        "title": "Ankle Sprains and Chronic Instability — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Lateral and medial ligament sprains of the ankle and chronic functional or mechanical instability after incomplete healing.",
        "summary": "ATFL and CFL are commonly injured in inversion. Chronic instability may require Broström repair or ligament reconstruction."
      },
